TAUCETI-VERDICT-ab60c35a589792ca9c2b4e55
{
  "verdict": "request_changes",
  "summary": "One public prelude theorem adds a parallel path-connectedness API where the existing `JoinedIn` API already supplies the same data.",
  "findings": [
    {
      "file": "TauCeti/AlgebraicTopology/FundamentalGroupoid/UniversalCoverPrelude.lean",
      "line": "64",
      "issue": "`IsPathConnected.exists_path` is a public wrapper around existing `IsPathConnected.joinedIn`/`JoinedIn.somePath`, creating a duplicate API for extracting a path with range in a path-connected set.",
      "fix": "Remove this theorem and replace uses with `let h := hU.joinedIn _ ha _ hb` followed by `h.somePath` and `h.somePath_mem`.",
      "evidence": "The theorem body itself is `let hab : JoinedIn U a b := hU.joinedIn _ ha _ hb; ⟨hab.somePath, Set.range_subset_iff.mpr hab.somePath_mem⟩`, showing the existing API directly provides the data."
    }
  ]
}
